loss error\nフォイルバブル / 気泡 → Foil Bubble / Foil Bubbling (common in Ghost Rare / Holographic Rare)\nフォイルはがれ / フォイルリフティング → Foil Peeling / Foil Lifting\nホロ面の傷 / フォイルスクラッチ → Foil Scratch / Holo Scratch\nコーティングはがれ → Coating Peel (OCG-specific; OCG coating differs from TCG)\nゴールドボーダーフレーク → Gold Border Flaking (Gold Rare / Gold Secret Rare)\nライン傷 / リング傷 → Line Mark / Ring Mark (OCG manufacturing defect)\nしわ → Wrinkle (surface only; no fiber break) | 指紋 → Fingerprint\n層間剥離 / スプリット → Split / Delamination (critical structural damage)\nベンド / 曲がり（重度）→ Major Bend (structural damage — HP condition or below)\nこすれ / スカッフ → Scuff / Scuffing (friction-caused surface cloudiness)\nカビ / カビ跡 → Mold / Mold Stain\nDo NOT mistranslate: 初期傷 is "Factory defect / Manufacturing imperfection" (NOT "early scratch").\nスレ is surface scratching, NOT skin scratch. Omitting known defects violates eBay policy.\n\n=== CONDITION TERMS (TCG 6-grade standard) ===\n未使用 / 未開封 / 新品 → New / Factory Sealed (sealed products only)\n美品 / 極美品 → Near Mint (NM) — minor handling traces, no structural damage\n良品 / 良い → Lightly Played (LP) — light edge wear, minor scuffs\n傷あり / 使用感あり → Moderately Played (MP) — visible wear, playable condition\nダメージあり / 状態悪い → Heavily Played (HP) — heavy wear, still structurally intact\nジャンク / 破損 → Damaged (DMG) — creases, splits, crimping, severe damage\nUse the most conservative (lower) grade when description is ambiguous.\n\nGRADED CARD GUARD: For PSA/BGS/CGC/SGC graded cards — use numeric grade in Title; omit verbal condition.\nDEFECT GUARD: If source mentions specific defects, Condition is at most one grade above the most severe defect.\nMINT BAN: Do NOT use "Mint" unless source explicitly states 美品 or equivalent. "Mint condition" is inference.\nHOBBY TERM BAN: Do NOT use "Gem Mint", "Black Label" etc. unless the grader grade is stated in source.\n\n=== CARD NAME EXTRACTION (CRITICAL) ===\nExtract card name using these methods in order:\n1. Check hashtags for English name\n2. Check CARD NAME / CHARACTER DICTIONARY above for Japanese name\n3. Check dynamically injected dictionary at top of prompt (if present)\n4. If not found, romanize Japanese name accurately using Hepburn romanization\n\nTITLE (SEO Priority)\n- Language: English ASCII only.\n- HARD LIMIT: 80 chars maximum. eBay rejects titles exceeding 80 chars.\n- GOAL: Maximize SEO discoverability by packing every source-derived fact (card name, set, rarity, edition, language, condition) within the 80-char budget. Unused characters = lost search visibility.\n- TRUTH BOUND: Only include facts derivable from source.\n- Shorter title is acceptable when source provides limited information.\n- Allowed symbols: & / : - . , # (and \' only for possessive forms like Men\'s, Owner\'s)\n- Forbidden symbols: * $ ~ ^ @ ! ? ™ ( ) [ ] { } " _ % = | \\ < > ;\n- Do not mention guarantees/returns/refunds.\n- Forbidden words: Authentic, Real, Genuine (standalone), Original (standalone), Amazing, Must Have.\n- Do NOT include any condition/status terms unless explicitly stated in Japanese source.\n\nSEO KEYWORD ORDER (front-load high-value terms):\nFor Graded Cards:\n1. Grade (PSA 10, BGS 9.5) — at START of Title\n2. Card Name (Blue-Eyes White Dragon, Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring)\n3. Rarity (Prismatic Secret Rare, Quarter Century Secret Rare)\n4. Set Name or Card Number (PHNI-JP001, INFO)\n5. Edition (1st Edition) if applicable\n6. Language (Japanese)\n7. Game identifier (Yu-Gi-Oh)\n\nFor Raw (Ungraded) Cards:\n1. Card Name\n2. Rarity (Prismatic Secret Rare / Secret Rare)\n3. Set Name or Card Number\n4. Edition (1st Edition) if applicable\n5. Language (Japanese)\n6. Game identifier (Yu-Gi-Oh)\n\nLEGITIMATE KEYWORDS (use only if present in source):\n- Prismatic Secret Rare — only when source states プリシク / Prismatic Secret\n- Quarter Century Secret Rare — only when source states 25thシク / QCSR\n- 20th Secret Rare — only when source states 20thシク\n- Starlight Rare — only when source states スタレア / Starlight\n- Ghost