wn, Red, Navy)\n  7. Hardware color if notable (GHW, SHW)\n  8. Missing accessories (No Box, No Papers - at end of Title)\n  9. Bonus SEO: Vintage, Rare, Limited (Category B — source-confirmed ONLY. See Rule 2)\n\nDESCRIPTION (SEO Priority)\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: Must contain brand + collection + product type (primary keywords).\n  Example: "This Louis Vuitton Monogram Zippy long wallet features the iconic monogram canvas with..."\n- Include searchable specs naturally:\n  * Collection/line name\n  * Material\n  * Color (exterior and interior if stated)\n  * Hardware color\n  * Dimensions (cm and inches) if stated\n  * Number of card slots, compartments if stated\n  * Serial number / date code location if present\n  * Included accessories (box, dust bag, papers)\n  * Made in country if stated (Made in France, Made in Italy, Made in Spain)\n- Use keyword variations: "wallet" "billfold" / "handbag" "purse" "bag" / "shoulder bag" "crossbody"\n- DEFECT/ISSUE REPORTING (CRITICAL):\n  If the source mentions ANY defect, malfunction, or issue, you MUST describe it in the Description.\n  DEFECT KEYWORDS AND TRANSLATIONS:\n    - 角スレ / 角擦れ -> "scuffed corners" or "corner wear"\n    - 擦れ / スレ -> "scuff marks" or "rubbing"\n    - 傷 -> "scratch"\n    - 色あせ / 退色 / 変色 -> "fading" or "discoloration"\n    - ほつれ -> "loose stitching" or "fraying"\n    - 剥がれ -> "peeling"\n    - べたつき / ベタ -> "stickiness" or "deterioration of interior coating"\n    - 型崩れ -> "loss of shape"\n    - 金具変色 / 金具くすみ -> "hardware tarnish" or "hardware discoloration"\n    - ファスナー不良 / ジッパー不良 -> "zipper malfunction"\n    - 内側汚れ / 内側シミ -> "interior stains"\n    - 外側汚れ -> "surface stains"\n    - 臭い / カビ臭 / タバコ臭 -> "odor"\n    - 持ち手劣化 -> "handle deterioration"\n    - 糸引き -> "thread pulling"\n    - コバ割れ / コバ剥がれ -> "edge cracks" or "glazing deterioration"\n    - 内側の剥がれ / 内張り剥がれ -> "interior peeling"\n    - 粉吹き / 内側粉吹き -> "interior flaking" or "powdering"\n    - メッキ剥がれ -> "hardware plating loss"\n    - 錆 / サビ -> "rust"\n    - 青錆 / 緑青 -> "verdigris"\n    - 持ち手ひび割れ -> "cracked handles"\n    - ファスナー固い -> "stiff zipper"\n    - ひび割れ -> "cracks" or "cracking"\n    - 日焼け / ヤケ -> "sun damage" or "tanning"\n    - ジャンク -> "for parts"\n    - 不具合 -> "defect"\n    - 〜できず / 〜不可 / 〜できません -> always means NOT possible. NEVER translate as "works" or "functional".\n  If source contains "(DEFECT: ...)" markers, use the English text directly.\n  Omitting known defects is a violation of eBay policy.\n- Describe condition only if clearly mentioned in source.\n- Avoid evaluative adjectives (excellent, good, mint, beautiful).\n- Exclude shipping/seller opinions/history/warranty.\n\nPRODUCTNAME\n- Format: [Brand] [Collection] [Product Type], English ASCII only.\n- Examples:\n  Louis Vuitton Monogram Zippy Wallet\n  Chanel Matelasse Chain Shoulder Bag\n  Hermes Birkin 30 Togo Handbag\n  Gucci GG Marmont Crossbody Bag\n  Prada Saffiano Bifold Wallet\n\nCATEGORY\n- Use eBay category style if determinable.\n- Wallets: Wallets\n- Handbags/Shoulder/Tote/Clutch: Bags & Handbags\n- Key Cases: Key Chains, Rings & Finders\n- Card Cases: ID & Document Holders\n- Belts: Belts\n- Pouches: Bags & Handbags\n- Backpacks: Backpacks\n- Briefcases: Briefcases & Laptop Bags\n- If unclear: N/A\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (exactly):\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\n\nVERIFICATION (must pass before returning):\n1. Title length 40-75 chars (target 68-75, shorter OK if source-bound, NEVER exceed 80).\n2. Description <= 480 chars.\n3. Only ASCII letters/numbers/spaces and allowed symbols (& / : - . ,) used throughout.\n4. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere.\n5. Title front-loads brand within first 30 chars (or material if unbranded).\n6. Description first sentence contains brand + product type keywords.\n7. ProductName uses real brand name (not N/A for brand).\n8. Condition/status words appear only if explicitly stated in source Japanese.\n9. No forbidden symbols in Title (no " \' ( ) [ ]).\n10. If source mentions any defect/malfunction, Description MUST include it.\n11. Every spec in the output must have a corresponding source in the Japanese text. If not found in source, it must NOT appear in output.\n12. Material claims match source exactly - do NOT assume leather type from brand alone.\n13. "Body Bag" is NEVER used. Use "Sling Bag" or "Waist Bag" instead.\n14. Seller inventory numbers (long digit sequences) are excluded from output.\n15. Dimensions appear in Description only (NOT in Title).\n16. If source mentions missing box/accessories, Title includes notation at end if space allows.\n\nIf any check fails, regenerate until all pass.\n\nInput: ${fullText}\n' };


