on notes / Defects\n- DEFECT REPORTING (CRITICAL): If source mentions ANY defect from DEFECT MAPPING, include it in Description.\n  Use EN translations from DEFECT MAPPING for accurate terminology.\n  Omitting known defects is a violation of eBay policy.\n- If AC 100V Japan model: include voltage warning sentence in Description.\n- BOUNDARY NOTE: If item is Pro Audio / Musical Instrument / PC / Camera, note:\n  "[Use appropriate prompt]"\n- Exclude: shipping terms, seller opinions, return policies, purchase history.\n\nPRODUCTNAME\n- Format: [Brand] [Model] [Product Type], English ASCII only\n- Include key spec or era descriptor if space allows\n- Examples:\n  Sony WH-1000XM5 Wireless Headphones\n  Pioneer PL-1200 Direct-Drive Turntable\n  Luxman L-550AXII Integrated Amplifier\n  Yamaha NS-1000M Studio Monitor Speakers\n  Panasonic TH-77EZ1000 OLED TV\n  Denon DP-1300MK2 Direct-Drive Turntable\n\nCATEGORY\nSelect ONE numeric eBay ID from CATEGORY ROUTING section above.\nIf item is out of scope (Pro Audio / Musical Instrument / PC / Camera), output: N/A\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT (exactly):\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\n\nCRITICAL: Never output a "Condition:" line.\nCRITICAL: Never output an "EbayCategory:" line.\n\nVERIFICATION (must pass before returning):\n1. Title is 80 chars or under HARD LIMIT.\n2. Description <= 480 chars.\n3. Only ASCII letters/numbers/spaces and allowed symbols (& / : - . , and apostrophe \' for possessives) used throughout.\n4. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere in output.\n5. Title front-loads Brand + Model + Type within the first 30 chars.\n6. Description first sentence contains Brand + Product type keywords.\n7. CATEGORY field uses one of the 9 valid eBay numeric IDs (112529 / 14990 / 14970 / 14988 / 14969 / 11071 / 170104 / 73368 / 50596) or N/A.\n8. Condition/status words appear only if explicitly stated in source.\n9. No forbidden symbols in Title (no " ( ) [ ]). Apostrophe \' allowed for possessives.\n10. If 