\nクリーチャー → Creature\nスペル / 魔法 → Spell\nトラップ / 罠 → Trap\nモンスター → Monster\nキャラクター / キャラ → Character\nイベント → Event\nオペレーション / オペ → Operation\nアクション → Action\nアイテム → Item\nランド / 土地 → Land\nレジェンドカード → Legend Card\nLRIG / ルリグ → LRIG\nフォワード → Forward (Final Fantasy TCG)\nバックアップ → Backup (Final Fantasy TCG)\nIf card type is not identifiable from source, leave CardType field as N/A.\n\n=== RARITY DICTIONARY ===\nUniversal codes — JP to EN:\nコモン → Common (C)\nアンコモン → Uncommon (UC)\nレア → Rare (R)\nスーパーレア → Super Rare (SR)\nウルトラレア → Ultra Rare (UR)\nシークレットレア / シークレット → Secret Rare (SEC)\nレジェンドレア → Legend Rare (LR)\nパラレル → Parallel\nホロ / キラ → Holo / Foil\nリバースホロ → Reverse Holo (RH)\nプロモ → Promo (P)\nサイン / 署名 → Signed\nGame-specific codes:\nCardfight Vanguard: RRR (Triple Rare) / RR (Double Rare) / OR (Over Rare) / XR (Extra Rare) / IMR (Imaginary Gift Rare)\nBattle Spirits: X Rare / XX Rare / Master Rare (MR)\nDuel Masters: VR (Very Rare) / DR (Double Rare)\nDisney Lorcana: Enchanted / Legendary (L)\nFlesh and Blood: Fabled / Majestic (M)\nWIXOSS: LRIG Rare (LR) / LRIG Common (LC)\nUNKNOWN RARITY: If rarity code is present in source but not in this dictionary, use it exactly as-is. Do NOT guess or fabricate rarity names.\n\n=== EDITION DICTIONARY ===\n初版 / 1st / 1版 → 1st Edition (CONDITIONAL: only when source explicitly confirms — never assume)\n日本語版 / 日本版 → Japanese (default assumption — always include for SEO)\n英語版 / EN edition → English (if source explicitly confirms)\nアジア英語版 / アジア版 → Asian English (if source explicitly confirms)\n韓国語版 → Korean (if source explicitly confirms)\n\n=== CONDITION TERMS ===\n未使用 / 未開封 / 新品 → New / Factory Sealed\n美品 / 極美品 → Near Mint (NM)\n良品 → Lightly Played (LP)\n並品 / 普通 → Moderately Played (MP)\n傷あり / 使用感あり → Moderately Played (MP)\nダメージあり / 状態悪い / 傷品 → Heavily Played (HP)\nジャンク / 破損 → Damaged (DMG)\nUse the most conservative (lower) grade when description is ambiguous.\nGRADED CARD GUARD: For PSA / BGS / CGC / SGC graded cards, use numeric grade only. Never add verbal condition (NM / LP / etc.) alongside grade.\nDEFECT GUARD: If source lists defects, condition must be LP or worse — never NM for a card with listed defects.\nMINT BAN: Never output "Mint" or "Gem Mint" as a standalone condition term. Use NM or the PSA 10 grade per context.\nHOBBY TERM BAN: Lightly Played / Moderately Played / Heavily Played are the standard TCG grades. Game-specific grades (e.g., Pokemon PSA-style "E4" grades) are not applicable to other games.\nAnti-mistranslation: 美品 = NM (NOT 良品 = LP). ジャンク / 破損 = DMG.\n\n=== LANGUAGE VARIATIONS ===\n日本語 / 日本版 → Japanese (always include in Title — high eBay SEO value)\n英語版 → English (if source explicitly confirms)\nアジア英語版 → Asian English (if source explicitly confirms)\n韓国語版 → Korean (if source explicitly confirms)\n繁体字中国語版 → Chinese Traditional (if source explicitly confirms)\n簡体字中国語版 → Chinese Simplified (if source explicitly confirms)\nAssume Japanese unless another language is explicitly stated in source.\n\n=== DEFECT MAPPING ===\nIf source explicitly states any defect, include in Description under "Condition Notes:". Omitting known defects is an eBay policy violation.\n折れ → Crease / Bent\n白かけ / 角スレ → Edge whitening / Corner wear\n色移り → Color transfer\nキラ剥がれ / ホロ剥がれ → Holo peeling\nセンタリング偏り → Off-centering\n擦れ / スレ → Surface scratches\n反り → Warping\n角ダメージ / 角折れ → Corner damage\nインク飛び → Print error\n初期傷 → Factory defect (NOT "early scratch")\n印刷ズレ / 枠ズレ → Print misalignment\n凹み → Dent\n水濡れ跡 → Water damage\nホロ浮き / フォイル浮き → Foil lifting\nフォイルバブル / 気泡 → Foil bubbling\nインク剥がれ → Ink peeling\n日焼け / 黄ばみ → Yellowing / Sun damage\nシミ / 汚れ → Stain / Soiling\n線傷 → Line scratch\n微細裂け → Micro tear\n分離 / 層剥離 → Delamination\n糊残り / 接着剤跡 → Adhesive residue\nテクスチャー剥がれ → Textured finish peeling\n色あせ / 変色 → Fading / Discoloration\nテープ跡 → Tape marks\n\n=== EXCLUDE FROM OUTPUT ===\nDo NOT include in any output field:\n- Shipping information (発送 / 送料 / shipping / 宅急便 / メルカリ便)\n- Seller opinions or purchase instructions\n- Storage and handling descriptions\n- Japanese hashtags not related to card name or set name\n- Pack / box types unless item itself is a sealed product\n\n=== TITLE ===\nHARD LIMIT: 80 chars maximum (eBay system limit — no exceptions).\nGOAL: Maximize buyer-relevant facts and SEO keyword density within the 80-char budget.\nTRUTH BOUND: Only facts derivable from source. Do NOT invent card names or game names not present in source.\nShorter OK: A sparse source produces a shorter accurate title — that beats a padded inaccurate one.\nALLOWED SYMBOLS: & / : - . , # (and \' for possessives)\nFORBIDDEN SYMBOLS: * $ ~ ^ @ ! ? ™ ( ) [ ] { } " _ % = | \\ < > ;\n"Japanese" is a high-value SEO term — always include when applicable.\nFor graded cards (PSA / BGS / CGC / SGC): grade at the START of title.\nTitle Composition Examples:\nGraded:  "PSA 10 Blaster Blade R Cardfight Vanguard Japanese"\nRaw:     "Blaster Blade R Cardfight Vanguard NM Japanese"\nLot:     "Cardfight Vanguard Japanese TCG Lot 20 Mixed Holo"\nSealed:  "Cardfight Vanguard Extra Booster Box Japanese Sealed"\nUnknown: "SR Holo Japanese Trading Card NM" (use available source facts only)\n\n=== DESCRIPTION ===\n- English ASCII only, <= 480 chars, single natural paragraph.\n- FIRST SENTENCE: must contain card name + game name.\n- Include when available: card name / game name / set name / card number / rarity / language / grade if graded.\n- If publisher is identifiable from source, include once: "Published by [Publisher]" using BRAND DICTIONARY for JP to EN.\n- If source states defects, include under "Condition Notes:" at end of Description.\n- NEVER include: shipping info / seller opinions / price negotiations / fabricated attributes.\n\n=== PRODUCTNAME ===\nFormat: [Card Name] [Rarity] [Set or Game Name]\nExample: Blaster Blade R Cardfight Vanguard\n\n=== CATEGORY ROUTING ===\nUngraded single card → 261328 (Trading Cards > Individual Cards)\nGraded card (PSA / BGS / CGC / SGC) → 261328 (Trading Cards > Individual Cards)\nMixed card lot → 183455 (Trading Cards > Mixed Lots)\nSealed booster pack / starter deck → 183456 (Trading Cards > Sealed Products)\nSealed booster box → 261044 (Trading Cards > Sealed Products)\nPromo card → 261328 (Trading Cards > Individual Cards)\nIf unclear → 261328 (Trading Cards > Individual Cards)\n\n=== SEO KEYWORD ORDER ===\nFront-load high-value terms to maximize visibility in eBay search.\nFor Graded Cards: Grade (PSA 10) → Card Name → Card Number → Rarity → Set Name → Language → Game Name\nFor Raw Cards: Card Name → Card Number → Rarity → Set Name → Condition (NM / LP) → Language → Game Name\nHigh-value terms: Japanese / 1st Edition / PSA 10 / Sealed / Holo / Rare / Alt Art / Parallel / Signed\nLEGITIMATE KEYWORDS — use only when source explicitly confirms:\n- PSA / BGS / CGC / SGC grade: only when source explicitly states graded card\n- 1st Edition: only when source explicitly states first edition\n- Parallel / Alt Art: only when source explicitly states alternate version\n- Signed: only when source explicitly states autographed card\n- Promo: only when source explicitly states promotional card\n- Foil / Holo / Reverse Holo: only when source explicitly states finish type\n- Secret Rare / Ultra Rare / Super Rare: only when rarity is stated in source\n- NM / LP: only when condition is stated in source\n\n=== OUTPUT FORMAT ===\nTitle: ...\nDescription: ...\nProductName: ...\nCategory: ...\nCardName: ...\nSetName: ...\nCardNumber: ...\nCardType: ...\nRarity: ...\nLanguage: ...\nGrade: ...\nCondition: ...\nYear: ...\nGame: ...\n\n=== VERIFICATION ===\n1. Title <= 80 chars and uses no FORBIDDEN SYMBOLS as defined in TITLE section.\n2. Description <= 480 chars, single paragraph, ASCII only, no CJK.\n3. No fabricated facts — every spec must derive from source.\n4. If graded card, grade appears at START of Title.\n5. If publisher identifiable from source, it appears once in Description.\n6. Card name appears in Title.\n7. Rarity code appears in Title if found in source.\n8. "Japanese" appears in Title unless source explicitly confirms another language.\n9. Game name appears in Title when space allows and source supports it.\n10. No shipping info or seller opinions in output.\n11. ProductName matches card name from Title.\n12. No CJK characters or emoji anywhere in output.\n13. Rule 2 compliance: no Category B marketing words without source evidence.\n14. All defects from source reported in Description under "Condition Notes:".\n15. No Bootleg / KO / Replica / Fake / Counterfeit / Authentic / Official anywhere in output.\n16. Game field is populated if game is identifiable from source.\nIf any check fails, regenerate until all pass.\n\nInput: ${fullText}\n' };


